From 33a7971ff5fa85e71a29af922e70bf3b9bef6258 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dfattal <dfattal@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 14:06:04 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 08/44] =?UTF-8?q?B4b:=20per-element=20inline-3D=20weave=20?=
 =?UTF-8?q?via=20CEF=20sub-rect=20model=20(#625)=20=E2=80=94=20WORKS=20in?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=20chrome?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Transplants the Step-A CEF external-compositor flow into Viz (design §13.3), so
the per-element weave fires end-to-end in real chrome — the per-element boundary
content_shell (page-flatten) architecturally could not cross. Eyeball: canvas
rect glasses-free 3D (when the Leia DP is tracking / in 3D mode), 2D chrome flat.

Pipeline: XRDisplayLayer reports the canvas window-relative device-px rect each
XR frame (XRSession::ReportInline3DRects) -> FrameWidget::SetInline3DRects ->
LayerTreeHost commit-state -> CompositorFrameMetadata.inline_3d_rects (new field
+ mojom array<gfx.mojom.Rect> + traits) -> SurfaceAggregator -> AggregatedFrame
-> Display::DrawAndSwap -> SkiaOutputSurface::SetInline3DRects -> (GPU thread)
SkiaOutputSurfaceImplOnGpu::MaybeWeaveOutput (replaces MaybeWeaveSubstitute),
post-Draw pre-Flush: readPixels the composited output sub-rect -> WeavePixels
(new provider method: CPU pixels -> intermediate texture -> CopyResource into the
keyed-mutex input) -> xrWeaveSubmitEXT (unchanged bridge) -> Leia DP weaves ->
import woven + fence-wait -> drawImageRect the woven back over the output.

Blink: inline-3d sessions now animate — treat a registered XRDisplayLayer as a
valid render state (MaybeRequestFrame), bypass the focus gate for inline-3d
(XRFrameProvider::ProcessScheduledFrame — a glasses-free display must weave
unfocused), and add a minimal inline-3d OnFrame path (no XR base layer/transport).

Validation-only launch flags (documented follow-ups, NOT the design):
--force_high_performance_gpu (match the NVIDIA adapter the Leia runtime uses;
dual-GPU cross-adapter NT-handle share was the final blocker),
--disable-features=TreesInViz (chrome default drops non-tracked_element_rects
metadata; follow-up: plumb inline_3d_rects through LayerContext) and SkiaGraphite
(CPU readback needs Ganesh synchronous readPixels; follow-up: Graphite async /
zero-copy D3D texture).

WIP checkpoint — still contains bring-up LOG diagnostics + a one-shot PNG/BGRA
dump; Item-4 (drop the now-dead B3a weave_target tag plumbing) not yet done.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
